In 1895 she entered into a mariage blanc with Gordon Woodhouse.

An important influence on her was Arnold Dolmetsch, a pioneer of the early music revival, who began making copies of old keyboard instruments in the 1890s.
In 1899 Violet performed Bach's Concerto for Three Harpsichords in C at a public concert in London.

In the 1930s she taught the Australian keyboard player Valda Aveling.
After Violet's death in 1948, aged 75, the two men remained at Nether Lypiatt until 1951, when Gordon died.

sentences: Violet Gordon-Woodhouse (23 April 1872 – 9 January 1948) was a British keyboard player.
As well as early music repertoire, Violet played music by nineteenth century composers and living composers such as Delius, who dedicated a harpsichord piece to her.
Dolmetsch worked abroad in the early-20th century, but Violet resumed her collaboration with him in 1910.
Later years ==
She lies in the churchyard of The Church of St Peter ad Vincula, Folkington, near Eastbourne, East Sussex.
She was close to many of the leading artists of her day, including Dame Ethel Smyth, Siegfried Sassoon, Irene, Lady Dean Paul (also known as Poldowski), and George Bernard Shaw.
